ead,Not my stories but 'tis what I think,I say I don't write poems, I just write dreams.\n\n- Sanhita\n|\nI'll fight it. I'll fight it for you. Don't you worry about me, Hazel Grace. I'm okay. I'll find a way to hang around and annoy you for a long time.\n\n- John Green, The Fault in Our Stars\n|\nOf all creatures that breathe and move upon the earth, nothing is bred that is weaker than man.\n\n- Homer, The Odyssey\n|\nNever give up. Things may be hard, but if you quit trying they'll never get better. Stop worrying and start trusting God. It will be worth it.\n\n- Germany\n|\nBy the way, if you get mad at your Mac laptop and wonder who designed this demonic device, notice the manufacturer's icon on top: an apple with a bite out of it.\n\n- Peter Kreeft, Jesus-Shock\n|\nMy life changed the day I moved beyond just wishing for things and I started earning them. That is the day I learned that we don't get what we wish for, we get what we work for.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nI do not need to grow up or train in the gym in order to beat the devil, when I know that my God can beat him for me.\n\n- Patience Johnson, Why Does an Orderly God Allow Disorder\n|\nIf you love deeply, you're going to get hurt badly. But it's still worth it.\n\n- C.S.\n|\nIf your dream is accepted by all, you don’t have a big enough dream. Big dreams challenge the status quo.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nSecond chances are not that important. What's important, is being ready when the first chance is given.\n\n- Jay\n|\nWe wrapped our dreams in words and patterned the words so that they would live forever, unforgettable.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, Fragile Things: Short Fictions and Wonders\n|\nWhat do you think Dimitri? Is this a good idea, Dimitri? Please give us your blessing so that we can fall down and worship you, Dimitri.\n\n- Richelle Mead, The Golden Lily\n|\nI use the terms 'sky' and 'earth' because as a human I cannot imagine those elements not be