ow many weeds envy it.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nthere are some poemsthat we leave behindsome that leave us behindwhile some just livesilentlyin the heartcrumble, sometimesdwindledisappeardieand are rebornwhen you smile again.\n\n- Sanober  Khan, Turquoise Silence\n|\nIn her crazy, upside down world, she needed someone like that. A rock that would keep her going, an anchor to keep her from drifting away. Instead, she was alone.\n\n- Kayla Krantz, Survive at Midnight\n|\nTrust because you are willing to accept the risk, not because it's safe or certain.\n\n- Aamir"